The paper deals with optimizing complex queries for massive data analysis, which is a common problem in database systems (cs.DB). The problem of multi-query optimization is essentially a combinatorial optimization problem, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper proposes a greedy algorithm for optimizing a linear transformation of the cost function, which involves making decisions based on certain assumptions, which is a common approach in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also discusses incorporating the proposed algorithm into existing transformation-based optimizers, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
